      "content": "For a safe buffer, I'd suggest aiming for at least 90 minutes between arriving at Paddington and your departure from King's Cross. This accounts for potential delays on the Heathrow Express, the transfer time through Paddington, and any unexpected slowdowns on the London Underground. It's always better to be a little early when dealing with city transit, especially with a tight connection. If you can afford a bit more time, aim for two hours to be truly comfortable.",
